  "venue_name": "Fort Lewis - Chambers Lake Area",
  "event_notes": "10am meet at Fort Lewis (Chambers Lake area). Connected to a three-day seminar at Pacific Lutheran University (Tacoma), sponsored by Presidents' Council on Physical Fitness; $1 fee for attendees not connected with the seminar. No restrooms or water; see newsletter for driving directions.\n\nMar/Apr 1979 recap: novice meet in Lake Chambers (Ft. Lewis Area 18) in conjunction with an orienteering seminar at PLU, sponsored by the Presidents' Council on Physical Fitness. Course: 5.4 km, 11 controls; progressed from straightforward to more difficult clues as participants gained confidence.",
